ECPR 51 - Discharge Prescription of Naloxone after Opioid Poisoning or Overdose

The patient presented with opioid poisoning or overdose.  {Blank single:19197::"Naloxone was prescribed, and the patient was educated about appropriate use of this medication.","Naloxone was distributed, and the patient was educated about appropriate use of this medication.","Naloxone was not prescribed due to patient allergy to medication.","The patient refused education about use of Naloxone."}